<p class=MsoBodyText2><span style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>Dear %FullName%,
</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span style='font-size:8.5pt;font-family:Verdana;
font-style:normal'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-size:10.0pt;font-family:Verdana;
font-style:normal'>          </span><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;
font-style:normal'>Here’s</span><span style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:
normal'> a quick note to let you know how I can help</span><span lang=EN
style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'> you or</span><span
style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'> anyone you might </span><span
lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>introduce</span><span
style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'> to me.</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>        Mike
is a very cyberspace-savvy guy, so when he was ready to trade apartment living
for a home of his own, he turned to the Internet for a loan.  He completed his
online application, started house hunting, and waited to hear from the Lender. 
After several weeks of not getting his calls returned promptly, not speaking to
the same person twice, and repeated requests for the same documentation, he’d
had enough and terminated the process.</span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana;font-style:normal'>&nbsp;</span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana'>         </span><span
lang=EN style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana'>Which left Mike back at
square one, until his coworker suggested Mike contact me.  When Mike asked if I
could just email information to him, I said,</span><span lang=EN
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana'> </span><span lang=EN
style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana'>“You deserve more than my email; you
deserve 20 minutes to sit down with a trusted advisor who will ask critical
questions, listen vigilantly, and craft a strategic plan for you.”  We put
together a mortgage with a great rate and terms, I stayed in touch with regular
updates, and the loan funded without incident.  Mike is still a very
cyberspace-savvy guy, but now he’s on his computer – in his new home.        </span></p>

<p class=MsoNormal><span lang=EN style='font-size:12.0pt;font-family:Verdana'>                                </span></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2 align=right style='text-align:right'><b><span
style='font-family:Verdana;color:purple;font-style:normal'>Fran Ferlazzo, Your
Personal Mortgage Consultant For Life</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2 align=right style='text-align:right;text-indent:.5in'><b><span
style='font-family:Verdana;color:purple;font-style:normal'>Lightning Mortgage,
866-822-8500 x102</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2 align=right style='text-align:right;text-indent:.5in'><b><span
style='font-family:Verdana;color:purple;font-style:normal'>&nbsp;</span></b></p>

<p class=MsoBodyText2><span lang=EN style='font-family:Verdana'>P.S.  Who’s the
next person you know who’s struggling in cyberspace instead of buying a home? 
Be sure to drop me an email to discuss how I can help them.</span></p>

